hor. <br>
<br>
The name of the rose totally rings a bell though, and I love historic novels, like Pillars of the Earth... I THINK I have seen the movie, but I only have vague memories of it for some reason. A medieval Connery and Slater sounds like a really interesting mix, although I think Connery is well, if not overrated, he is more appreciated for his personal style and presence, rather than his acting abilities -- he's kinda like a really interesting person, and more or less just acts himself, whether he's reclusive author, a Soviet submarine captain, or an immortal sword fighter. <br>
<br>
Hmmmmm, but that really was a good movie as far as I can remember, I should keep an eye out for it, thanks for reminding me. <br>
<br>
Lotsa a good movies never get noticed though, sadly. And garbage like Star Wars sells. <br>
- Lets go watch a movie, guys! <br>
- No, lets not! Lets go watch some mindless garbage with the plot of Sesame Street episode, acting skills of a Mexican soap opera, and characters nearly -- but not quite -- as interesting as the crew on Friends! <br>
- Why, that sounds horrible, I don't wanna watch that! <br>
- But it has laser sword fights! <br>
- Whoa, lets go! <br>
<br>
And that's not just here, but everywhere around the world. <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/unandiinsunfang.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NandiinSunfang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/18/01 11:50:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about a film</span><hr size=1> Fucault's Pendulum is tougher to read than The Name of the Rose in my opinion.<br>
<br>
I saw Umberto Eco one day on TV, trying to explain to a guy something. Guy was completely lost and U. Eco stated something simple :<br>
&quot;I'm brilliant, you're not, and i'm not going to lower the quality of my explanation just because you can't understand me&quot;.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, that guy is not an arrogant guy. He's just brilliant, and if 99% of the population can't grab what he's saying, too bad for them.<br>
<br>
Well, i have to admit, i didn't understand all he said. I think i got his point but i'm not even sure 'bout that :-)<br>
<br>
Shinolai Luneclaire<br>
