Being brilliant is easy. Being understood is hard. The audience may be guilty of being less than brilliant, I have no argument with that. But if he is unable to modify his message to accomodate the abilities of the audience, then he may be lacking in brilliance also. If he is able, but unwilling, then he is lazy and/or arrogant. <br>
<br>
